    "body": "<!-- Before reporting: search existing issues and check the FAQ. -->\r\n\r\n- `nvim --version`:\r\n$ nvim --version    \r\nNVIM v0.4.4         \r\nBuild type: Release \r\nLuaJIT 2.1.0-beta3  \r\n\r\n- Operating system/version:\r\nmacOS Big Sur version 11.1\r\n- Terminal name/version:\r\nmac standard terminal version 2.11\r\n- `$TERM`:\r\nscreen-256color\r\n\r\n<!--\r\nIf this report is about different behaviour between Nvim and Vim, make sure to\r\nread `:h vim-differences` first. Otherwise remove the next line.\r\n-->\r\n[x] `vim -u DEFAULTS` (version: ) behaves differently\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce using `nvim -u NORC`\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ nvim --noplugin /tmp/hoge2.txt -u NONE \r\n: colorscheme blue                       \r\n: hi StatusLine ctermbg=1            \r\nThen, try to insert Japanese character    \r\n```\r\n[hoge2.txt](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/files/6654682/hoge2.txt)\r\n\r\n### Actual behaviour\r\n- when trying to input Japanese Language, the line is \r\nhighlighted the same color defined by StatusLine      \r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/23188902/122032989-212c2480-cd9e-11eb-9909-ef85893d79e6.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n### Expected behaviour\r\n- No highlight is expected for the line.\r\n\r\n### Other info\r\n- Highlighted color is same as the StatusLine.                              \r\n- If we change the setting for StatusLine, then the highlighted color       \r\n\tchanged accordingly.                                                      \r\n\t- example                                                                 \r\n\t\t:hi StatusLine ctermbg=1                                                \r\n- The problem happens when trying to input Japanese language in insert mode \r\n   No problem when trying to input alphabet                                  \r\n- The problem happens when using nvim.                     \r\n   No problem with vim (8.2)                                                 \r\n- The problem does not happen when the window size is half by using vsplit  \r\n- The problem happens on mac, not windows.                                  \r\n- This problem does not always happens. But probability is very high.            \r\n- This problem happens with following colorscheme                           \r\n\t- blue                                                                    \r\n\t- darkblue                                                                \r\n   but not happens with following colorscheme                                     \r\n\t- default                                                                 \r\n\t- delek                                                                   \r\n\r\n",
